  "aiDescription": {
    "summary": "The \"Get Miva customers\" export retrieves customer data from the Miva application. It uses the Miva assistant and makes an HTTP POST request to the \"/json.mvc\" endpoint. The export uses pagination to retrieve multiple pages of data and expects a JSON response. It handles both success and error responses in JSON format. The export has a test configuration with a limit of 1 record and a REST configuration with the same endpoint and request body. It also has a transform configuration and a filter configuration to modify and filter the data. The export has an adaptor type of \"RESTExport\".",
    "detailed": "This export is named \"Get Miva customers\" and its description states that it retrieves all customers from Miva that have been modified since the last time this flow ran. \n\nThe export is of type \"test\" and the assistant used is \"miva\". \n\nThe export is not a one-to-many export, meaning it does not treat child records as main records for this step in the flow. \n\nThe export uses the \"customers\" resource and the \"v1\" version of the Miva assistant. The operation used is \"customerlist_load_query\". \n\nThe export makes an HTTP POST request to the \"/json.mvc\" endpoint. The request body contains the store code and the function \"CustomerList_Load_Query\". The \"Count\" parameter is set to 1, and the \"Miva_Request_Timestamp\" is set to the current timestamp. \n\nThe export expects a JSON response and handles both success and error responses in JSON format. \n\nThe export uses pagination to retrieve multiple pages of data. The pagination method used is \"body\", and the last-page status code is set to 404. The request body for subsequent pages includes the offset, store code, function, count, and timestamp parameters. \n\nThe response data is expected to be in the \"data.data\" path. The success path in the response body is \"success\", and the export allows an array for the success path. \n\nThe export has a raw data value of \"64a84f79d3075444fb9fb2b031ed0e6bf64640d5bec66d6aaced5b70\". \n\nThe export has a test configuration with a limit of 1 record. \n\nThe export also has a REST configuration with the same endpoint and request body as the HTTP configuration. The response data is expected to be in the \"data.data\" path, and the success path is \"success\". \n\nThe export has a transform configuration of type \"expression\" with an expression version of \"1\". \n\nThe export has a filter configuration of type \"expression\" with an expression version of \"1\". The filter rules specify that the export should only include records that have a \"dt_created\" value greater than the last export date. \n\nThe export has an input filter configuration of type \"expression\" with an expression version of \"1\". \n\nThe export has an adaptor type of \"RESTExport\". \n\nOverall, this export retrieves customer data from the Miva application using an HTTP or REST API. It paginates through the results, applies a filter to include only modified records, and transforms the data using an expression.",
    "generatedOn": null
  },
